de.tudresden.inf.rn.mobilis.sea.pubsub.model.tree

Class StatisticsFacade

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tudresden.inf.rn.mobilis.sea.pubsub.model.tree.StatisticsFacade
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICurrentGameData, ICurrentHeatMapData, ICurrentPlayerData, ICurrentPositionData, ICurrentPrognosisData, ICurrentTeamData

    public class StatisticsFacade
extends java.lang.Object
implements ICurrentPositionData, ICurrentPlayerData, ICurrentTeamData, ICurrentHeatMapData, ICurrentPrognosisData, ICurrentGameData
    The StatisticsFacade is used to bundle all available interfaces of the StatisticCollection into one auxiliary proxy. For multi-thread purposes it is also capable to delegate calls to a free resource. So you may get at any time the current StatisticCollection which then will not be filled with new data again (until you release it by getting it again)
